{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_011wZc6Yp3wLgud7rNN6S1rN","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have all the information needed. Let me create a comprehensive summary of the findings.\n\n## Summary: Referral System DB Interface and Configuration\n\nBased on my thorough read of `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/db.ts` and `config.ts`, here's the complete referral system structure:\n\n### 1. **Referral-Related Interfaces** (Lines 127-177 in db.ts)\n\n```typescript\nexport interface ReferralCode {\n  id: number;\n  wallet: string;\n  code: string;\n  created_at: Date;\n  updated_at: Date;\n}\n\nexport interface ReferralLink {\n  id: number;\n  referrer_wallet: string;\n  referee_wallet: string;\n  created_at: Date;\n}\n\nexport interface ReferralEarning {\n  id: number;\n  referrer_wallet: string;\n  referee_wallet: string;\n  round_id: string;\n  game_type: string;\n  wager_lamports: number;\n  fee_lamports: number;\n  referrer_earned_lamports: number;\n  referrer_rate_bps: number;\n  referee_rebate_lamports: number;\n  referee_rebate_rate_bps: number;\n  created_at: Date;\n}\n\nexport interface ReferralStats {\n  referred_count: number;\n  active_count: number;\n  total_volume_lamports: string;\n  total_earned_lamports: string;\n  pending_lamports: string;\n}\n\nexport interface ReferralClaim {\n  id: string;\n  wallet: string;\n  amount_lamports: string;\n  status: \"pending\" | \"processing\" | \"completed\" | \"failed\";\n  tx_signature: string | null;\n  error: string | null;\n  requested_at: Date;\n  processed_at: Date | null;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Method Signatures in Db Interface** (Lines 313-407 in db.ts)\n\n**Referral Codes:**\n```typescript\ninsertReferralCode(wallet: string, code: string): Promise<ReferralCode>;\ngetReferralCodeByWallet(wallet: string): Promise<ReferralCode | undefined>;\ngetReferralCodeByCode(code: string): Promise<ReferralCode | undefined>;\nupsertReferralCode(wallet: string, code: string): Promise<ReferralCode>;\n```\n\n**Referral Links:**\n```typescript\ninsertReferralLink(referrerWallet: string, refereeWallet: string): Promise<ReferralLink>;\ngetReferralLinkByReferee(refereeWallet: string): Promise<ReferralLink | undefined>;\ngetReferralLinksByReferrer(referrerWallet: string): Promise<ReferralLink[]>;\n```\n\n**Earnings & Stats:**\n```typescript\ninsertReferralEarning(params: {\n  referrerWallet: string;\n  refereeWallet: string;\n  roundId: string;\n  gameType: string;\n  wagerLamports: number;\n  feeLamports: number;\n  referrerEarnedLamports: number;\n  referrerRateBps: number;\n  refereeRebateLamports: number;\n  refereeRebateRateBps: number;\n}): Promise<ReferralEarning>;\n\ngetPendingBalance(wallet: string): Promise<string>;\ngetReferralEarnings(wallet: string, page: number, limit: number): Promise<{ items: ReferralEarning[]; totalPages: number }>;\ngetReferralStats(wallet: string): Promise<ReferralStats>;\n```\n\n**Claims & Rates:**\n```typescript\ninsertReferralClaim(wallet: string, amountLamports: string): Promise<ReferralClaim>;\ngetReferralClaim(claimId: string): Promise<ReferralClaim | undefined>;\nupdateClaimStatus(\n  claimId: string,\n  status: ReferralClaim[\"status\"],\n  meta?: { txSignature?: string; error?: string },\n): Promise<ReferralClaim>;\ngetReferrerRate(wallet: string, defaultRateBps: number): Promise<number>;\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Implementations** (Lines 771-963 in db.ts)\n\n**Code Methods:**\n```typescript\nasync insertReferralCode(wallet, code) {\n  const rows = await sql<ReferralCode[]>`\n    INSERT INTO referral_codes (wallet, code)\n    VALUES (${wallet}, ${code})\n    RETURNING *\n  `;\n  return rows[0]!;\n}\n\nasync getReferralCodeByWallet(wallet) {\n  const rows = await sql<ReferralCode[]>`\n    SELECT * FROM referral_codes WHERE wallet = ${wallet}\n  `;\n  return rows[0];\n}\n\nasync getReferralCodeByCode(code) {\n  const rows = await sql<ReferralCode[]>`\n    SELECT * FROM referral_codes WHERE code = ${code}\n  `;\n  return rows[0];\n}\n\nasync upsertReferralCode(wallet, code) {\n  const rows = await sql<ReferralCode[]>`\n    INSERT INTO referral_codes (wallet, code)\n    VALUES (${wallet}, ${code})\n    ON CONFLICT (wallet) DO UPDATE SET\n      code = ${code},\n      updated_at = now()\n    RETURNING *\n  `;\n  return rows[0]!;\n}\n```\n\n**Link Methods:**\n```typescript\nasync insertReferralLink(referrerWallet, refereeWallet) {\n  const rows = await sql<ReferralLink[]>`\n    INSERT INTO referral_links (referrer_wallet, referee_wallet)\n    VALUES (${referrerWallet}, ${refereeWallet})\n    RETURNING *\n  `;\n  return rows[0]!;\n}\n\nasync getReferralLinkByReferee(refereeWallet) {\n  const rows = await sql<ReferralLink[]>`\n    SELECT * FROM referral_links WHERE referee_wallet = ${refereeWallet}\n  `;\n  return rows[0];\n}\n\nasync getReferralLinksByReferrer(referrerWallet) {\n  const rows = await sql<ReferralLink[]>`\n    SELECT * FROM referral_links WHERE referrer_wallet = ${referrerWallet}\n    ORDER BY created_at DESC\n  `;\n  return rows;\n}\n```\n\n**Earnings Methods:**\n```typescript\nasync insertReferralEarning(params) {\n  const rows = await sql<ReferralEarning[]>`\n    INSERT INTO referral_earnings (\n      referrer_wallet, referee_wallet, round_id, game_type,\n      wager_lamports, fee_lamports,\n      referrer_earned_lamports, referrer_rate_bps,\n      referee_rebate_lamports, referee_rebate_rate_bps\n    ) VALUES (...)\n    RETURNING *\n  `;\n  return normalizeReferralEarning(rows[0]!);\n}\n\nasync getPendingBalance(wallet) {\n  // Returns SUM(referrer_earned) + SUM(referee_rebate) - SUM(claimed amounts)\n  // Result: string (lamports)\n}\n\nasync getReferralEarnings(wallet, page, limit) {\n  // Returns { items: ReferralEarning[], totalPages: number }\n  // Filtered: referrer_wallet = wallet\n  // Order: created_at DESC\n  // Pagination: (page - 1) * limit offset\n}\n\nasync getReferralStats(wallet) {\n  // Returns ReferralStats with:\n  // - referred_count: total count of referral_links where referrer_wallet = wallet\n  // - active_count: distinct referees with earnings in last 7 days\n  // - total_volume_lamports: sum of wager_lamports (string)\n  // - total_earned_lamports: sum of referrer_earned_lamports (string)\n  // - pending_lamports: calculated balance (string)\n}\n```\n\n**Claim Methods:**\n```typescript\nasync insertReferralClaim(wallet, amountLamports) {\n  const rows = await sql<ReferralClaim[]>`\n    INSERT INTO referral_claims (wallet, amount_lamports, status)\n    VALUES (${wallet}, ${amountLamports}, 'pending')\n    RETURNING *\n  `;\n  return rows[0]!;\n}\n\nasync getReferralClaim(claimId) {\n  const rows = await sql<ReferralClaim[]>`\n    SELECT * FROM referral_claims WHERE id = ${claimId}\n  `;\n  return rows[0];\n}\n\nasync updateClaimStatus(claimId, status, meta) {\n  const rows = await sql<ReferralClaim[]>`\n    UPDATE referral_claims\n    SET\n      status = ${status},\n      tx_signature = COALESCE(${meta?.txSignature ?? null}, tx_signature),\n      error = COALESCE(${meta?.error ?? null}, error),\n      processed_at = ${status === \"completed\" || status === \"failed\" ? sql`now()` : sql`processed_at`}\n    WHERE id = ${claimId}\n    RETURNING *\n  `;\n  return rows[0]!;\n}\n\nasync getReferrerRate(wallet, defaultRateBps) {\n  const rows = await sql<{ rate_bps: number }[]>`\n    SELECT rate_bps FROM referral_kol_rates WHERE wallet = ${wallet}\n  `;\n  return rows[0]?.rate_bps ?? defaultRateBps;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Config Interface and loadConfig()** (config.ts)\n\n```typescript\nexport interface Config {\n  port: number;\n  databaseUrl: string;\n  dbSchema: string;\n  rpcUrl: string;\n  wsRpcUrl: string | undefined;\n  serverKeypair: Keypair;\n  jwtSecret: Uint8Array;\n  cluster: string;\n  challengeTtlSeconds: number;\n  accessTokenTtlSeconds: number;\n  refreshTokenTtlDays: number;\n  rateLimitPerWallet: number;\n  rateLimitGlobal: number;\n  workerPollIntervalMs: number;\n  entropyAccount: string;\n  pythBtcUsdAccount: string;\n  minSolBalance: number;\n  eventQueuePollMs: number;\n  referralDefaultRateBps: number;        // Default: 1000 bps (10%)\n  referralMinClaimLamports: number;      // Default: 10000000 lamports (0.01 SOL)\n}\n\nexport function loadConfig(): Config {\n  return {\n    // ... other fields\n    referralDefaultRateBps: parseInt(\n      process.env.REFERRAL_DEFAULT_RATE_BPS ?? \"1000\",\n      10,\n    ),\n    referralMinClaimLamports: parseInt(\n      process.env.REFERRAL_MIN_CLAIM_LAMPORTS ?? \"10000000\",\n      10,\n    ),\n  };\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Error Handling Pattern**\n\n**For \"not found\" cases:**\n- **Returns `undefined`**: `getReferralCodeByWallet()`, `getReferralCodeByCode()`, `getReferralLinkByReferee()`, `getReferralClaim()`\n- **Returns empty array**: `getReferralLinksByReferrer()` returns `Promise<ReferralLink[]>` (never throws)\n- **Throws on error**: `insertReferralCode()` throws on duplicate wallet/code constraint violation\n- **Throws on error**: `insertReferralLink()` throws on duplicate referee constraint violation\n\n**For update/insert operations:**\n- Use `RETURNING *` to get the modified row\n- Access with `rows[0]!` (asserts non-empty)\n- `upsertReferralCode()` uses `ON CONFLICT (wallet) DO UPDATE` pattern\n- `updateClaimStatus()` conditionally sets `processed_at = now()` only when status is \"completed\" or \"failed\"\n\n**String handling (numeric values):**\n- Large sums returned as `string` (e.g., `pending_lamports`, `total_volume_lamports`)\n- Normalized via `normalizeReferralEarning()` function (lines 439-449) which converts `number` fields\n- `getPendingBalance()` and SQL aggregates return `string` type to preserve precision for large sums\n\n---\n\n### Key Observations\n\n1. **No rate-limiting at DB level** — rates are fetched from `referral_kol_rates` table with fallback to `defaultRateBps`\n2. **Claim status lifecycle**: `pending` → `processing` → `completed` OR `failed`\n3. **Pending balance calculation is transactional**: sums earnings minus completed claims\n4. **Active count filters**: only counts distinct referees with earnings in last 7 days\n5. **All `insert` operations throw on constraint violations** — no silent ignores except `ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING` for transactions"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a37785e7ac2a26e06 (use SendMessage with to: 'a37785e7ac2a26e06' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 55487\ntool_uses: 6\nduration_ms: 47139</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9bf9a501-ff1b-418f-8f9a-7e40ba9d0165","uuid":"1001f27a-6f4b-423c-8840-7e9b80c0f697","timestamp":"2026-03-25T11:52:06.565Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"In /workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/db.ts, find and show:\n\n1. The referral-related interfaces (ReferralCode, ReferralLink, etc.)\n2. The method signatures in the Db interface for referral operations (insertReferralCode, getReferralCodeByWallet, getReferralCodeByCode, upsertReferralCode)\n3. The implementations of these methods in createDb()\n4. The Config interface and loadConfig() function (especially referralDefaultRateBps and referralMinClaimLamports)\n5. How other methods handle errors/not-found cases\n\nBe thorough - show the actual code signatures and return types.","agentId":"a37785e7ac2a26e06","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have all the information needed. Let me create a comprehensive summary of the findings.\n\n## Summary: Referral System DB Interface and Configuration\n\nBased on my thorough read of `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/db.ts` and `config.ts`, here's the complete referral system structure:\n\n### 1. **Referral-Related Interfaces** (Lines 127-177 in db.ts)\n\n```typescript\nexport interface ReferralCode {\n  id: number;\n  wallet: string;\n  code: string;\n  created_at: Date;\n  updated_at: Date;\n}\n\nexport interface ReferralLink {\n  id: number;\n  referrer_wallet: string;\n  referee_wallet: string;\n  created_at: Date;\n}\n\nexport interface ReferralEarning {\n  id: number;\n  referrer_wallet: string;\n  referee_wallet: string;\n  round_id: string;\n  game_type: string;\n  wager_lamports: number;\n  fee_lamports: number;\n  referrer_earned_lamports: number;\n  referrer_rate_bps: number;\n  referee_rebate_lamports: number;\n  referee_rebate_rate_bps: number;\n  created_at: Date;\n}\n\nexport interface ReferralStats {\n  referred_count: number;\n  active_count: number;\n  total_volume_lamports: string;\n  total_earned_lamports: string;\n  pending_lamports: string;\n}\n\nexport interface ReferralClaim {\n  id: string;\n  wallet: string;\n  amount_lamports: string;\n  status: \"pending\" | \"processing\" | \"completed\" | \"failed\";\n  tx_signature: string | null;\n  error: string | null;\n  requested_at: Date;\n  processed_at: Date | null;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Method Signatures in Db Interface** (Lines 313-407 in db.ts)\n\n**Referral Codes:**\n```typescript\ninsertReferralCode(wallet: string, code: string): Promise<ReferralCode>;\ngetReferralCodeByWallet(wallet: string): Promise<ReferralCode | undefined>;\ngetReferralCodeByCode(code: string): Promise<ReferralCode | undefined>;\nupsertReferralCode(wallet: string, code: string): Promise<ReferralCode>;\n```\n\n**Referral Links:**\n```typescript\ninsertReferralLink(referrerWallet: string, refereeWallet: string): Promise<ReferralLink>;\ngetReferralLinkByReferee(refereeWallet: string): Promise<ReferralLink | undefined>;\ngetReferralLinksByReferrer(referrerWallet: string): Promise<ReferralLink[]>;\n```\n\n**Earnings & Stats:**\n```typescript\ninsertReferralEarning(params: {\n  referrerWallet: string;\n  refereeWallet: string;\n  roundId: string;\n  gameType: string;\n  wagerLamports: number;\n  feeLamports: number;\n  referrerEarnedLamports: number;\n  referrerRateBps: number;\n  refereeRebateLamports: number;\n  refereeRebateRateBps: number;\n}): Promise<ReferralEarning>;\n\ngetPendingBalance(wallet: string): Promise<string>;\ngetReferralEarnings(wallet: string, page: number, limit: number): Promise<{ items: ReferralEarning[]; totalPages: number }>;\ngetReferralStats(wallet: string): Promise<ReferralStats>;\n```\n\n**Claims & Rates:**\n```typescript\ninsertReferralClaim(wallet: string, amountLamports: string): Promise<ReferralClaim>;\ngetReferralClaim(claimId: string): Promise<ReferralClaim | undefined>;\nupdateClaimStatus(\n  claimId: string,\n  status: ReferralClaim[\"status\"],\n  meta?: { txSignature?: string; error?: string },\n): Promise<ReferralClaim>;\ngetReferrerRate(wallet: string, defaultRateBps: number): Promise<number>;\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Implementations** (Lines 771-963 in db.ts)\n\n**Code Methods:**\n```typescript\nasync insertReferralCode(wallet, code) {\n  const rows = await sql<ReferralCode[]>`\n    INSERT INTO referral_codes (wallet, code)\n    VALUES (${wallet}, ${code})\n    RETURNING *\n  `;\n  return rows[0]!;\n}\n\nasync getReferralCodeByWallet(wallet) {\n  const rows = await sql<ReferralCode[]>`\n    SELECT * FROM referral_codes WHERE wallet = ${wallet}\n  `;\n  return rows[0];\n}\n\nasync getReferralCodeByCode(code) {\n  const rows = await sql<ReferralCode[]>`\n    SELECT * FROM referral_codes WHERE code = ${code}\n  `;\n  return rows[0];\n}\n\nasync upsertReferralCode(wallet, code) {\n  const rows = await sql<ReferralCode[]>`\n    INSERT INTO referral_codes (wallet, code)\n    VALUES (${wallet}, ${code})\n    ON CONFLICT (wallet) DO UPDATE SET\n      code = ${code},\n      updated_at = now()\n    RETURNING *\n  `;\n  return rows[0]!;\n}\n```\n\n**Link Methods:**\n```typescript\nasync insertReferralLink(referrerWallet, refereeWallet) {\n  const rows = await sql<ReferralLink[]>`\n    INSERT INTO referral_links (referrer_wallet, referee_wallet)\n    VALUES (${referrerWallet}, ${refereeWallet})\n    RETURNING *\n  `;\n  return rows[0]!;\n}\n\nasync getReferralLinkByReferee(refereeWallet) {\n  const rows = await sql<ReferralLink[]>`\n    SELECT * FROM referral_links WHERE referee_wallet = ${refereeWallet}\n  `;\n  return rows[0];\n}\n\nasync getReferralLinksByReferrer(referrerWallet) {\n  const rows = await sql<ReferralLink[]>`\n    SELECT * FROM referral_links WHERE referrer_wallet = ${referrerWallet}\n    ORDER BY created_at DESC\n  `;\n  return rows;\n}\n```\n\n**Earnings Methods:**\n```typescript\nasync insertReferralEarning(params) {\n  const rows = await sql<ReferralEarning[]>`\n    INSERT INTO referral_earnings (\n      referrer_wallet, referee_wallet, round_id, game_type,\n      wager_lamports, fee_lamports,\n      referrer_earned_lamports, referrer_rate_bps,\n      referee_rebate_lamports, referee_rebate_rate_bps\n    ) VALUES (...)\n    RETURNING *\n  `;\n  return normalizeReferralEarning(rows[0]!);\n}\n\nasync getPendingBalance(wallet) {\n  // Returns SUM(referrer_earned) + SUM(referee_rebate) - SUM(claimed amounts)\n  // Result: string (lamports)\n}\n\nasync getReferralEarnings(wallet, page, limit) {\n  // Returns { items: ReferralEarning[], totalPages: number }\n  // Filtered: referrer_wallet = wallet\n  // Order: created_at DESC\n  // Pagination: (page - 1) * limit offset\n}\n\nasync getReferralStats(wallet) {\n  // Returns ReferralStats with:\n  // - referred_count: total count of referral_links where referrer_wallet = wallet\n  // - active_count: distinct referees with earnings in last 7 days\n  // - total_volume_lamports: sum of wager_lamports (string)\n  // - total_earned_lamports: sum of referrer_earned_lamports (string)\n  // - pending_lamports: calculated balance (string)\n}\n```\n\n**Claim Methods:**\n```typescript\nasync insertReferralClaim(wallet, amountLamports) {\n  const rows = await sql<ReferralClaim[]>`\n    INSERT INTO referral_claims (wallet, amount_lamports, status)\n    VALUES (${wallet}, ${amountLamports}, 'pending')\n    RETURNING *\n  `;\n  return rows[0]!;\n}\n\nasync getReferralClaim(claimId) {\n  const rows = await sql<ReferralClaim[]>`\n    SELECT * FROM referral_claims WHERE id = ${claimId}\n  `;\n  return rows[0];\n}\n\nasync updateClaimStatus(claimId, status, meta) {\n  const rows = await sql<ReferralClaim[]>`\n    UPDATE referral_claims\n    SET\n      status = ${status},\n      tx_signature = COALESCE(${meta?.txSignature ?? null}, tx_signature),\n      error = COALESCE(${meta?.error ?? null}, error),\n      processed_at = ${status === \"completed\" || status === \"failed\" ? sql`now()` : sql`processed_at`}\n    WHERE id = ${claimId}\n    RETURNING *\n  `;\n  return rows[0]!;\n}\n\nasync getReferrerRate(wallet, defaultRateBps) {\n  const rows = await sql<{ rate_bps: number }[]>`\n    SELECT rate_bps FROM referral_kol_rates WHERE wallet = ${wallet}\n  `;\n  return rows[0]?.rate_bps ?? defaultRateBps;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Config Interface and loadConfig()** (config.ts)\n\n```typescript\nexport interface Config {\n  port: number;\n  databaseUrl: string;\n  dbSchema: string;\n  rpcUrl: string;\n  wsRpcUrl: string | undefined;\n  serverKeypair: Keypair;\n  jwtSecret: Uint8Array;\n  cluster: string;\n  challengeTtlSeconds: number;\n  accessTokenTtlSeconds: number;\n  refreshTokenTtlDays: number;\n  rateLimitPerWallet: number;\n  rateLimitGlobal: number;\n  workerPollIntervalMs: number;\n  entropyAccount: string;\n  pythBtcUsdAccount: string;\n  minSolBalance: number;\n  eventQueuePollMs: number;\n  referralDefaultRateBps: number;        // Default: 1000 bps (10%)\n  referralMinClaimLamports: number;      // Default: 10000000 lamports (0.01 SOL)\n}\n\nexport function loadConfig(): Config {\n  return {\n    // ... other fields\n    referralDefaultRateBps: parseInt(\n      process.env.REFERRAL_DEFAULT_RATE_BPS ?? \"1000\",\n      10,\n    ),\n    referralMinClaimLamports: parseInt(\n      process.env.REFERRAL_MIN_CLAIM_LAMPORTS ?? \"10000000\",\n      10,\n    ),\n  };\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Error Handling Pattern**\n\n**For \"not found\" cases:**\n- **Returns `undefined`**: `getReferralCodeByWallet()`, `getReferralCodeByCode()`, `getReferralLinkByReferee()`, `getReferralClaim()`\n- **Returns empty array**: `getReferralLinksByReferrer()` returns `Promise<ReferralLink[]>` (never throws)\n- **Throws on error**: `insertReferralCode()` throws on duplicate wallet/code constraint violation\n- **Throws on error**: `insertReferralLink()` throws on duplicate referee constraint violation\n\n**For update/insert operations:**\n- Use `RETURNING *` to get the modified row\n- Access with `rows[0]!` (asserts non-empty)\n- `upsertReferralCode()` uses `ON CONFLICT (wallet) DO UPDATE` pattern\n- `updateClaimStatus()` conditionally sets `processed_at = now()` only when status is \"completed\" or \"failed\"\n\n**String handling (numeric values):**\n- Large sums returned as `string` (e.g., `pending_lamports`, `total_volume_lamports`)\n- Normalized via `normalizeReferralEarning()` function (lines 439-449) which converts `number` fields\n- `getPendingBalance()` and SQL aggregates return `string` type to preserve precision for large sums\n\n---\n\n### Key Observations\n\n1. **No rate-limiting at DB level** — rates are fetched from `referral_kol_rates` table with fallback to `defaultRateBps`\n2. **Claim status lifecycle**: `pending` → `processing` → `completed` OR `failed`\n3. **Pending balance calculation is transactional**: sums earnings minus completed claims\n4. **Active count filters**: only counts distinct referees with earnings in last 7 days\n5. **All `insert` operations throw on constraint violations** — no silent ignores except `ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING` for transactions"}],"totalDurationMs":47139,"totalTokens":55487,"totalToolUseCount":6,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":360,"cache_read_input_tokens":51905,"output_tokens":3222,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_