{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01TP2vt2gVQWAytPQvUJrUk6","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now let me create a comprehensive summary document with all the information gathered:\n\n## Backend Service Architecture Summary\n\nBased on my thorough exploration of `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/`, here's a complete guide to the routing, auth, and database patterns:\n\n### 1. **Router Framework: Hono**\n\nThe backend uses **Hono** (modern, lightweight web framework for Node.js/Edge), not Express. All routes are defined using Hono's fluent API.\n\n**Main entry point**: `/services/backend/src/index.ts` (lines 1-230)\n\n**Key characteristics**:\n- Framework: `import { Hono } from \"hono\"`\n- Server: `@hono/node-server` with `serve()` function\n- CORS enabled globally with `*` origin\n- Request logging middleware for all routes (DEBUG level)\n\n### 2. **Route Registration Pattern**\n\nRoutes are registered in `index.ts` using a factory + mounting pattern:\n\n```typescript\n// Factory function returns a Hono app instance\nconst authRoutes = createAuthRoutes({\n  authDb,\n  jwtSecret,\n  cluster,\n  challengeTtlSeconds,\n  accessTokenTtlSeconds,\n  refreshTokenTtlDays,\n});\n\n// Mount at a path\napp.route(\"/auth\", authRoutes);\n```\n\n**Complete route registration structure** (from index.ts):\n\n| Path | Type | Auth | Factory | Deps |\n|------|------|------|---------|------|\n| `/auth` | POST | None | `createAuthRoutes()` | authDb, jwtSecret, cluster, TTLs |\n| `/profile` | GET/POST | JWT (requireAllMethods: true) | `createProfileRoutes()` | db |\n| `/fairness/coinflip` | POST | JWT | `createCoinflipRoutes()` | db, connection, serverKeypair, pdaWatcher |\n| `/fairness/lord` | POST | JWT | `createLordRoutes()` | db, connection, serverKeypair, pdaWatcher |\n| `/fairness/rounds` | GET | None | `createRoundsRoutes()` | db |\n| `/closecall` | GET/POST | JWT | `createCloseCallRoutes()` | db, connection, serverKeypair, clockWorker, sql |\n| `/price` | GET | None | `createPriceRoutes()` | none |\n| `/health` | GET | None | `createHealthRoutes()` | db, sql, connection, serverKey, isWorkerRunning |\n\n### 3. **JWT Authentication Middleware**\n\n**File**: `/services/backend/src/middleware/jwt-auth.ts`\n\n**How it works**:\n\n1. Verifies HS256 JWT in `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header\n2. Extracts wallet address from `payload.sub` claim\n3. **Sets `c.set(\"wallet\", payload.sub)`** for downstream handlers to access via `c.get(\"wallet\")`\n4. Middleware is **applied per-route-group** before mounting routes\n\n**Key code pattern**:\n\n```typescript\n// In index.ts\napp.use(\"/fairness/*\", createJwtAuthMiddleware({ jwtSecret }));\napp.route(\"/fairness/coinflip\", createCoinflipRoutes(...));\n\n// In routes/create.ts (POST handler)\napp.post(\"/create\", async (c) => {\n  const jwtWallet = c.get(\"wallet\") as string | undefined;\n  // JWT wallet can be verified against body.wallet for defense-in-depth\n});\n```\n\n**JWT middleware config options**:\n- `jwtSecret: Uint8Array` — HMAC secret\n- `requireAllMethods?: boolean` — if true, enforces JWT for ALL HTTP methods (default: POST only)\n\n**Behavior**:\n- GET requests: pass through unless `requireAllMethods: true`\n- POST requests: require valid JWT (401 if missing/invalid/expired)\n- Returns `{ error: \"...\" }` on auth failure with 401 status\n\n### 4. **Rate Limiting Middleware**\n\n**File**: `/services/backend/src/middleware/rate-limit.ts`\n\n**Applied to**:\n- `/auth/*` — 20 reqs/wallet, global limit, 60s window\n- `/fairness/*` — configurable per-wallet + global, 60s window\n\n**How it works**:\n\n```typescript\nexport interface RateLimitConfig {\n  perWallet: number;      // Max requests per wallet per window\n  global: number;         // Max total requests per window\n  windowMs: number;       // Window size (e.g., 60_000)\n}\n```\n\n- Uses **in-memory sliding window** (resets on restart)\n- Extracts wallet from:\n  1. JWT context (set by JWT middleware) — preferred\n  2. Request body `{ wallet: \"...\" }` — for pre-auth routes\n  3. IP headers (`x-forwarded-for` / `x-real-ip`) — fallback for auth routes\n\n- Returns **429 Too Many Requests** with `Retry-After` header\n\n### 5. **Complete Route File Example: `/routes/create.ts` (Coinflip)**\n\n**Path**: `/services/backend/src/routes/create.ts` (243 lines)\n\n**Endpoint**: `POST /fairness/coinflip/create`\n\n**Complete handler flow**:\n\n```typescript\nexport function createCoinflipRoutes(deps: CreateRoutesDeps) {\n  const { db, connection, serverKeypair, pdaWatcher } = deps;\n  const app = new Hono<AppEnv>();\n\n  app.post(\"/create\", async (c) => {\n    // 1. Parse + validate JSON body\n    const body = validateBody(await c.req.json());\n    \n    // 2. Verify wallet matches JWT (defense-in-depth)\n    const jwtWallet = c.get(\"wallet\") as string | undefined;\n    if (jwtWallet && body.wallet !== jwtWallet) {\n      return c.json({ error: \"Wallet does not match authenticated session\" }, 403);\n    }\n    \n    // 3. Validate public key\n    const creatorPubkey = new PublicKey(body.wallet);\n    \n    // 4-5. Generate secret, commitment, matchId, derive PDA\n    const secret = generateSecret();\n    const commitment = computeCommitment(secret);\n    const matchId = generateMatchId();\n    const [matchPda] = deriveMatchPda(creatorPubkey, matchId);\n    \n    // 6. Check for duplicate in DB\n    const existing = await db.getRoundByPda(matchPda.toBase58());\n    if (existing) return c.json({ error: \"Match ID collision — please retry\" }, 409);\n    \n    // 7. Build + partial-sign transaction\n    const result = await buildCreateMatchTx({ ... });\n    \n    // 8. Store round in DB\n    await db.insertRound({\n      pda: matchPdaStr,\n      game: \"coinflip\",\n      creator: body.wallet,\n      serverKey: serverKeypair.publicKey.toBase58(),\n      secret,\n      commitment,\n      amountLamports: body.amountLamports,\n      side: body.side,\n      matchId: matchId.toString(\"hex\"),\n      phase: \"created\",\n    });\n    \n    // 9. Write operator event\n    await db.insertOperatorEvent(matchPdaStr, \"secret_generated\", { ... });\n    \n    // 10. Subscribe PDA to WebSocket watcher for instant join detection\n    pdaWatcher?.watch(matchPdaStr);\n    \n    return c.json({\n      transaction,\n      matchPda: matchPdaStr,\n      matchId: matchId.toString(\"hex\"),\n      commitment: commitment.toString(\"hex\"),\n      lastValidBlockHeight,\n    });\n  });\n\n  return app;\n}\n```\n\n**Request body shape**:\n```typescript\ninterface CreateRequestBody {\n  wallet: string;              // base58 public key\n  amountLamports: number;      // min 1_000_000, max 100_000_000_000\n  side: number;                // 0 (Heads) or 1 (Tails)\n}\n```\n\n**Response shape**:\n```json\n{\n  \"transaction\": \"base64-serialized-tx\",\n  \"matchPda\": \"11111...\",\n  \"matchId\": \"0a1b2c3d...\",\n  \"commitment\": \"abc123...\",\n  \"lastValidBlockHeight\": 123456789\n}\n```\n\n### 6. **Profile Routes Example: `/routes/profile.ts` (Authenticated)**\n\n**Path**: `/services/backend/src/routes/profile.ts` (143 lines)\n\n**Endpoints**:\n- `GET /profile/transactions` — requires JWT for ALL methods\n- `POST /profile/confirm-tx` — player reports confirmed tx\n\n**Key patterns**:\n\n```typescript\nexport function createProfileRoutes(deps: ProfileRoutesDeps) {\n  const { db } = deps;\n  const app = new Hono<AppEnv>();\n\n  app.get(\"/transactions\", async (c) => {\n    const wallet = c.get(\"wallet\");  // Extract from JWT context\n    if (!wallet) return c.json({ error: \"Authentication required\" }, 401);\n\n    // Parse pagination cursor + filters\n    const cursor = c.req.query(\"cursor\");\n    const limit = Math.min(Math.max(parseInt(c.req.query(\"limit\") ?? \"20\", 10) || 20, 1), 50);\n    const dbGame = TO_DB_GAME[c.req.query(\"game\")];\n\n    const rows = await db.getTransactions(wallet, cursor, limit, dbGame);\n    \n    const transactions = rows.map((row) => ({\n      id: row.id,\n      game: GAME_TO_FRONTEND[row.game] ?? row.game,\n      matchId: row.match_id,\n      txType: row.tx_type,\n      amountLamports: String(row.amount_lamports),\n      txSig: row.tx_sig,\n      createdAt: row.created_at.toISOString(),\n    }));\n\n    const nextCursor = transactions.length === limit\n      ? String(transactions[transactions.length - 1]!.id)\n      : null;\n\n    return c.json({ transactions, nextCursor });\n  });\n\n  app.post(\"/confirm-tx\", async (c) => {\n    const wallet = c.get(\"wallet\");\n    if (!wallet) return c.json({ error: \"Authentication required\" }, 401);\n\n    const body = await c.req.json();\n    // Validate game, matchId, txType, txSig, amountLamports\n    // Map game name: coinflip → coinflip, lord-of-rngs → lord, close-call → closecall\n    \n    await db.insertTransaction({\n      wallet,\n      game: dbGame,\n      matchId: body.matchId,\n      txType: body.txType,\n      amountLamports: body.amountLamports,\n      txSig: body.txSig,\n    });\n\n    return c.json({ ok: true });\n  });\n\n  return app;\n}\n```\n\n**Game name mapping** (for API/DB consistency):\n```typescript\nconst TO_DB_GAME = {\n  \"coinflip\": \"coinflip\",\n  \"lord\": \"lord\",\n  \"closecall\": \"closecall\",\n  \"lord-of-rngs\": \"lord\",          // Frontend name\n  \"close-call\": \"closecall\",        // Frontend name\n};\nconst GAME_TO_FRONTEND = {\n  \"coinflip\": \"coinflip\",\n  \"lord\": \"lord-of-rngs\",\n  \"closecall\": \"close-call\",\n};\n```\n\n### 7. **Round Verification Routes: `/routes/rounds.ts` (Public)**\n\n**Path**: `/services/backend/src/routes/rounds.ts` (220 lines)\n\n**Endpoints** (no JWT required):\n- `GET /fairness/rounds/history?game=coinflip&limit=20` — recently settled rounds\n- `GET /fairness/rounds/by-id/:matchId` — fetch round by 16-char hex ID or numeric timestamp\n- `GET /fairness/rounds/:pda` — fetch round by PDA address\n\n**Key behaviors**:\n\n```typescript\napp.get(\"/:pda\", async (c) => {\n  const pda = c.req.param(\"pda\");\n  const round = await db.getRoundByPda(pda);\n  if (!round) return c.json({ error: \"Round not found\" }, 404);\n  \n  return c.json(await formatRoundResponse(db, round));\n});\n\n// formatRoundResponse conditionally includes secret ONLY for settled rounds\nfunction buildRoundResponse(round: Round, settlePayload: ...) {\n  const isSettled = round.phase === \"settled\";\n  const response = { pda, game, phase, creator, commitment, ... };\n  \n  if (isSettled) {\n    response.secret = round.secret.toString(\"hex\");  // Revealed post-settlement\n    response.resultHash = ...;\n    response.winner = ...;\n    response.settleTx = ...;\n    response.verification = {\n      commitmentCheck: \"sha256(secret) == commitment\",\n      resultFormula: \"sha256(secret || entropy || pda || algorithmVersion)\",\n      entropySource: \"SlotHashes sysvar at target_slot\",\n    };\n  }\n  \n  return response;\n}\n```\n\n### 8. **Hono Environment Type Definition**\n\n**File**: `/services/backend/src/hono-env.ts`\n\n```typescript\nexport type AppEnv = {\n  Variables: {\n    wallet: string;  // Set by JWT middleware via c.set(\"wallet\", ...)\n  };\n};\n```\n\n**Usage in routes**:\n```typescript\nconst app = new Hono<AppEnv>();  // Enables type-safe c.get(\"wallet\")\n```\n\n### 9. **Database Access in Routes**\n\n**Db interface** (from `/services/backend/src/db.ts`):\n\nRoutes receive a **typed Db client** with methods like:\n\n```typescript\nexport interface Db {\n  getRoundByPda(pda: string): Promise<Round | undefined>;\n  getRoundByMatchId(matchId: string): Promise<Round | undefined>;\n  insertRound(params: InsertRoundParams): Promise<void>;\n  updateRoundPhase(pda: string, phase: RoundPhase, metadata?: Record<string, unknown>): Promise<void>;\n  insertOperatorEvent(pda: string, eventType: OperatorEventType, payload: unknown): Promise<void>;\n  getLatestOperatorEvent(pda: string, eventType: OperatorEventType): Promise<OperatorEvent | undefined>;\n  getTransactions(wallet: string, cursor?: string, limit?: number, game?: string): Promise<Transaction[]>;\n  insertTransaction(params: InsertTransactionParams): Promise<void>;\n  getUnsettledStats(): Promise<{ count: number; oldestAgeSeconds: number }>;\n  getRecentSettledRounds(game: string, limit: number): Promise<Round[]>;\n  // ... more methods\n}\n```\n\n**Db dependency injection**:\n```typescript\n// In index.ts\nconst db = createDb(config.databaseUrl);\n\n// Passed to route factories\napp.route(\"/fairness/coinflip\", createCoinflipRoutes({ db, connection, serverKeypair }));\n```\n\n### 10. **Error Response Format**\n\nAll error responses follow a consistent pattern:\n\n```typescript\n// 400 — Bad request\nc.json({ error: \"Invalid request body\" }, 400);\n\n// 401 — Authentication required\nc.json({ error: \"Missing or invalid Authorization header\" }, 401);\n\n// 403 — Forbidden (e.g., wallet mismatch)\nc.json({ error: \"Wallet does not match authenticated session\" }, 403);\n\n// 404 — Not found\nc.json({ error: \"Round not found\" }, 404);\n\n// 409 — Conflict (e.g., duplicate match ID)\nc.json({ error: \"Match ID collision — please retry\" }, 409);\n\n// 429 — Rate limit exceeded\nc.header(\"Retry-After\", \"60\");\nc.json({ error: \"Too many requests\" }, 429);\n\n// 500 — Server error\nc.json({ error: \"Failed to build transaction\" }, 500);\n\n// 503 — Service unavailable\nc.json({ error: \"Price unavailable\" }, 503);\n\n// 204 — No content (successful logout)\nc.body(null, 204);\n```\n\n### 11. **Auth Routes: Challenge-Response Flow**\n\n**File**: `/services/backend/src/routes/auth.ts` (287 lines)\n\n**Complete JWT session lifecycle**:\n\n```typescript\n// POST /auth/challenge\n{\n  \"wallet\": \"11111...\"\n}\n→ Response:\n{\n  \"nonce\": \"32-hex-chars\",\n  \"message\": \"Sign in to RNG Utopia\\nWallet: ...\\nNonce: ...\",\n  \"expiresAt\": \"2026-03-25T12:34:56Z\"\n}\n\n// POST /auth/verify — sign challenge message with wallet private key\n{\n  \"nonce\": \"...\",\n  \"wallet\": \"...\",\n  \"signature\": \"base58-ed25519-signature\"\n}\n→ Response:\n{\n  \"accessToken\": \"jwt-hs256\",\n  \"accessExpiresAt\": \"2026-03-25T12:35:56Z\",\n  \"refreshToken\": \"opaque-48-byte-hex\",\n  \"refreshExpiresAt\": \"2026-04-24T12:34:56Z\"\n}\n\n// POST /auth/refresh — rotate tokens\n{\n  \"refreshToken\": \"opaque-48-byte-hex\"\n}\n→ Response:\n{\n  \"accessToken\": \"new-jwt\",\n  \"accessExpiresAt\": \"...\",\n  \"refreshToken\": \"new-opaque-token\",\n  \"refreshExpiresAt\": \"...\"\n}\n\n// POST /auth/logout — revoke token\n{\n  \"refreshToken\": \"...\"\n}\n→ Response: 204 (No Content)\n```\n\n**Key details**:\n- JWT: HS256, `sub` claim = wallet address\n- Refresh tokens: opaque 48-byte hex, stored as SHA256 hash in DB\n- Token reuse detection: revokes entire token family if replay detected\n- TTL defaults: access = 1 hour, refresh = 7 days\n\n### 12. **Health & Status Routes**\n\n**File**: `/services/backend/src/routes/health.ts` (90 lines)\n\n```typescript\napp.get(\"/health\", async (c) => {\n  const verbose = c.req.query(\"verbose\") === \"1\";\n  \n  // Queries DB for:\n  // - unsettledCount\n  // - oldestUnsettledAge\n  \n  // Queries RPC for:\n  // - server keypair SOL balance\n  \n  return c.json({\n    status: \"ok\",\n    version: \"0.1.0\",\n    serverKey: \"...\",\n    solBalance: 1.5,\n    dbConnected: true,\n    workerRunning: true,\n    unsettledCount: 3,\n    oldestUnsettledAge: 245,\n    eventQueue: { pending: 2, processing: 0, dead: 0, completed: 156 },  // if verbose=1\n  });\n});\n```\n\n### 13. **Summary Table: Common Patterns**\n\n| Pattern | Location | Usage |\n|---------|----------|-------|\n| Hono app instance | Every route factory | `const app = new Hono<AppEnv>()` |\n| JWT context variable | JWT middleware → route handlers | `c.get(\"wallet\")` |\n| Dependency injection | Route factory params | `createCoinflipRoutes({ db, connection, ... })` |\n| Error responses | All routes | `c.json({ error: \"...\" }, status)` |\n| Logging | All routes | `logger.info()`, `logger.warn()`, `logger.error()` |\n| DB queries | All authenticated routes | `db.getRoundByPda()`, `db.insertRound()` |\n| PDA watching | Coinflip/Lord routes | `pdaWatcher?.watch(pda)` |\n| Rate limiting | Auth & fairness routes | Sliding window per-wallet + global |\n\nThis is a comprehensive, production-grade backend with clean separation of concerns, type safety via TypeScript, and security best practices (JWT verification, wallet validation, rate limiting, defense-in-depth checks)."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a99fc934ff03d1644 (use SendMessage with to: 'a99fc934ff03d1644' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 66124\ntool_uses: 15\nduration_ms: 80896</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9bf9a501-ff1b-418f-8f9a-7e40ba9d0165","uuid":"a0064387-4d87-4386-a8fa-fa8b8cae5622","timestamp":"2026-03-25T11:52:36.488Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the backend service at /workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/ to understand:\n\n1. How routes are structured (look at existing route files in routes/ dir)\n2. How JWT auth middleware is applied to routes\n3. How routes are registered/mounted in index.ts or the main app file\n4. What the router pattern looks like (Hono? Express? Other?)\n5. How the Db instance is accessed in route handlers\n6. The error response format used\n\nLook at 2-3 route files for full patterns. Show the complete code of at least one route file and the route registration section in the main index file. Also check what the JWT auth middleware returns (wallet address, etc.)\n\nThoroughness: very thorough","agentId":"a99fc934ff03d1644","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now let me create a comprehensive summary document with all the information gathered:\n\n## Backend Service Architecture Summary\n\nBased on my thorough exploration of `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/`, here's a complete guide to the routing, auth, and database patterns:\n\n### 1. **Router Framework: Hono**\n\nThe backend uses **Hono** (modern, lightweight web framework for Node.js/Edge), not Express. All routes are defined using Hono's fluent API.\n\n**Main entry point**: `/services/backend/src/index.ts` (lines 1-230)\n\n**Key characteristics**:\n- Framework: `import { Hono } from \"hono\"`\n- Server: `@hono/node-server` with `serve()` function\n- CORS enabled globally with `*` origin\n- Request logging middleware for all routes (DEBUG level)\n\n### 2. **Route Registration Pattern**\n\nRoutes are registered in `index.ts` using a factory + mounting pattern:\n\n```typescript\n// Factory function returns a Hono app instance\nconst authRoutes = createAuthRoutes({\n  authDb,\n  jwtSecret,\n  cluster,\n  challengeTtlSeconds,\n  accessTokenTtlSeconds,\n  refreshTokenTtlDays,\n});\n\n// Mount at a path\napp.route(\"/auth\", authRoutes);\n```\n\n**Complete route registration structure** (from index.ts):\n\n| Path | Type | Auth | Factory | Deps |\n|------|------|------|---------|------|\n| `/auth` | POST | None | `createAuthRoutes()` | authDb, jwtSecret, cluster, TTLs |\n| `/profile` | GET/POST | JWT (requireAllMethods: true) | `createProfileRoutes()` | db |\n| `/fairness/coinflip` | POST | JWT | `createCoinflipRoutes()` | db, connection, serverKeypair, pdaWatcher |\n| `/fairness/lord` | POST | JWT | `createLordRoutes()` | db, connection, serverKeypair, pdaWatcher |\n| `/fairness/rounds` | GET | None | `createRoundsRoutes()` | db |\n| `/closecall` | GET/POST | JWT | `createCloseCallRoutes()` | db, connection, serverKeypair, clockWorker, sql |\n| `/price` | GET | None | `createPriceRoutes()` | none |\n| `/health` | GET | None | `createHealthRoutes()` | db, sql, connection, serverKey, isWorkerRunning |\n\n### 3. **JWT Authentication Middleware**\n\n**File**: `/services/backend/src/middleware/jwt-auth.ts`\n\n**How it works**:\n\n1. Verifies HS256 JWT in `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header\n2. Extracts wallet address from `payload.sub` claim\n3. **Sets `c.set(\"wallet\", payload.sub)`** for downstream handlers to access via `c.get(\"wallet\")`\n4. Middleware is **applied per-route-group** before mounting routes\n\n**Key code pattern**:\n\n```typescript\n// In index.ts\napp.use(\"/fairness/*\", createJwtAuthMiddleware({ jwtSecret }));\napp.route(\"/fairness/coinflip\", createCoinflipRoutes(...));\n\n// In routes/create.ts (POST handler)\napp.post(\"/create\", async (c) => {\n  const jwtWallet = c.get(\"wallet\") as string | undefined;\n  // JWT wallet can be verified against body.wallet for defense-in-depth\n});\n```\n\n**JWT middleware config options**:\n- `jwtSecret: Uint8Array` — HMAC secret\n- `requireAllMethods?: boolean` — if true, enforces JWT for ALL HTTP methods (default: POST only)\n\n**Behavior**:\n- GET requests: pass through unless `requireAllMethods: true`\n- POST requests: require valid JWT (401 if missing/invalid/expired)\n- Returns `{ error: \"...\" }` on auth failure with 401 status\n\n### 4. **Rate Limiting Middleware**\n\n**File**: `/services/backend/src/middleware/rate-limit.ts`\n\n**Applied to**:\n- `/auth/*` — 20 reqs/wallet, global limit, 60s window\n- `/fairness/*` — configurable per-wallet + global, 60s window\n\n**How it works**:\n\n```typescript\nexport interface RateLimitConfig {\n  perWallet: number;      // Max requests per wallet per window\n  global: number;         // Max total requests per window\n  windowMs: number;       // Window size (e.g., 60_000)\n}\n```\n\n- Uses **in-memory sliding window** (resets on restart)\n- Extracts wallet from:\n  1. JWT context (set by JWT middleware) — preferred\n  2. Request body `{ wallet: \"...\" }` — for pre-auth routes\n  3. IP headers (`x-forwarded-for` / `x-real-ip`) — fallback for auth routes\n\n- Returns **429 Too Many Requests** with `Retry-After` header\n\n### 5. **Complete Route File Example: `/routes/create.ts` (Coinflip)**\n\n**Path**: `/services/backend/src/routes/create.ts` (243 lines)\n\n**Endpoint**: `POST /fairness/coinflip/create`\n\n**Complete handler flow**:\n\n```typescript\nexport function createCoinflipRoutes(deps: CreateRoutesDeps) {\n  const { db, connection, serverKeypair, pdaWatcher } = deps;\n  const app = new Hono<AppEnv>();\n\n  app.post(\"/create\", async (c) => {\n    // 1. Parse + validate JSON body\n    const body = validateBody(await c.req.json());\n    \n    // 2. Verify wallet matches JWT (defense-in-depth)\n    const jwtWallet = c.get(\"wallet\") as string | undefined;\n    if (jwtWallet && body.wallet !== jwtWallet) {\n      return c.json({ error: \"Wallet does not match authenticated session\" }, 403);\n    }\n    \n    // 3. Validate public key\n    const creatorPubkey = new PublicKey(body.wallet);\n    \n    // 4-5. Generate secret, commitment, matchId, derive PDA\n    const secret = generateSecret();\n    const commitment = computeCommitment(secret);\n    const matchId = generateMatchId();\n    const [matchPda] = deriveMatchPda(creatorPubkey, matchId);\n    \n    // 6. Check for duplicate in DB\n    const existing = await db.getRoundByPda(matchPda.toBase58());\n    if (existing) return c.json({ error: \"Match ID collision — please retry\" }, 409);\n    \n    // 7. Build + partial-sign transaction\n    const result = await buildCreateMatchTx({ ... });\n    \n    // 8. Store round in DB\n    await db.insertRound({\n      pda: matchPdaStr,\n      game: \"coinflip\",\n      creator: body.wallet,\n      serverKey: serverKeypair.publicKey.toBase58(),\n      secret,\n      commitment,\n      amountLamports: body.amountLamports,\n      side: body.side,\n      matchId: matchId.toString(\"hex\"),\n      phase: \"created\",\n    });\n    \n    // 9. Write operator event\n    await db.insertOperatorEvent(matchPdaStr, \"secret_generated\", { ... });\n    \n    // 10. Subscribe PDA to WebSocket watcher for instant join detection\n    pdaWatcher?.watch(matchPdaStr);\n    \n    return c.json({\n      transaction,\n      matchPda: matchPdaStr,\n      matchId: matchId.toString(\"hex\"),\n      commitment: commitment.toString(\"hex\"),\n      lastValidBlockHeight,\n    });\n  });\n\n  return app;\n}\n```\n\n**Request body shape**:\n```typescript\ninterface CreateRequestBody {\n  wallet: string;              // base58 public key\n  amountLamports: number;      // min 1_000_000, max 100_000_000_000\n  side: number;                // 0 (Heads) or 1 (Tails)\n}\n```\n\n**Response shape**:\n```json\n{\n  \"transaction\": \"base64-serialized-tx\",\n  \"matchPda\": \"11111...\",\n  \"matchId\": \"0a1b2c3d...\",\n  \"commitment\": \"abc123...\",\n  \"lastValidBlockHeight\": 123456789\n}\n```\n\n### 6. **Profile Routes Example: `/routes/profile.ts` (Authenticated)**\n\n**Path**: `/services/backend/src/routes/profile.ts` (143 lines)\n\n**Endpoints**:\n- `GET /profile/transactions` — requires JWT for ALL methods\n- `POST /profile/confirm-tx` — player reports confirmed tx\n\n**Key patterns**:\n\n```typescript\nexport function createProfileRoutes(deps: ProfileRoutesDeps) {\n  const { db } = deps;\n  const app = new Hono<AppEnv>();\n\n  app.get(\"/transactions\", async (c) => {\n    const wallet = c.get(\"wallet\");  // Extract from JWT context\n    if (!wallet) return c.json({ error: \"Authentication required\" }, 401);\n\n    // Parse pagination cursor + filters\n    const cursor = c.req.query(\"cursor\");\n    const limit = Math.min(Math.max(parseInt(c.req.query(\"limit\") ?? \"20\", 10) || 20, 1), 50);\n    const dbGame = TO_DB_GAME[c.req.query(\"game\")];\n\n    const rows = await db.getTransactions(wallet, cursor, limit, dbGame);\n    \n    const transactions = rows.map((row) => ({\n      id: row.id,\n      game: GAME_TO_FRONTEND[row.game] ?? row.game,\n      matchId: row.match_id,\n      txType: row.tx_type,\n      amountLamports: String(row.amount_lamports),\n      txSig: row.tx_sig,\n      createdAt: row.created_at.toISOString(),\n    }));\n\n    const nextCursor = transactions.length === limit\n      ? String(transactions[transactions.length - 1]!.id)\n      : null;\n\n    return c.json({ transactions, nextCursor });\n  });\n\n  app.post(\"/confirm-tx\", async (c) => {\n    const wallet = c.get(\"wallet\");\n    if (!wallet) return c.json({ error: \"Authentication required\" }, 401);\n\n    const body = await c.req.json();\n    // Validate game, matchId, txType, txSig, amountLamports\n    // Map game name: coinflip → coinflip, lord-of-rngs → lord, close-call → closecall\n    \n    await db.insertTransaction({\n      wallet,\n      game: dbGame,\n      matchId: body.matchId,\n      txType: body.txType,\n      amountLamports: body.amountLamports,\n      txSig: body.txSig,\n    });\n\n    return c.json({ ok: true });\n  });\n\n  return app;\n}\n```\n\n**Game name mapping** (for API/DB consistency):\n```typescript\nconst TO_DB_GAME = {\n  \"coinflip\": \"coinflip\",\n  \"lord\": \"lord\",\n  \"closecall\": \"closecall\",\n  \"lord-of-rngs\": \"lord\",          // Frontend name\n  \"close-call\": \"closecall\",        // Frontend name\n};\nconst GAME_TO_FRONTEND = {\n  \"coinflip\": \"coinflip\",\n  \"lord\": \"lord-of-rngs\",\n  \"closecall\": \"close-call\",\n};\n```\n\n### 7. **Round Verification Routes: `/routes/rounds.ts` (Public)**\n\n**Path**: `/services/backend/src/routes/rounds.ts` (220 lines)\n\n**Endpoints** (no JWT required):\n- `GET /fairness/rounds/history?game=coinflip&limit=20` — recently settled rounds\n- `GET /fairness/rounds/by-id/:matchId` — fetch round by 16-char hex ID or numeric timestamp\n- `GET /fairness/rounds/:pda` — fetch round by PDA address\n\n**Key behaviors**:\n\n```typescript\napp.get(\"/:pda\", async (c) => {\n  const pda = c.req.param(\"pda\");\n  const round = await db.getRoundByPda(pda);\n  if (!round) return c.json({ error: \"Round not found\" }, 404);\n  \n  return c.json(await formatRoundResponse(db, round));\n});\n\n// formatRoundResponse conditionally includes secret ONLY for settled rounds\nfunction buildRoundResponse(round: Round, settlePayload: ...) {\n  const isSettled = round.phase === \"settled\";\n  const response = { pda, game, phase, creator, commitment, ... };\n  \n  if (isSettled) {\n    response.secret = round.secret.toString(\"hex\");  // Revealed post-settlement\n    response.resultHash = ...;\n    response.winner = ...;\n    response.settleTx = ...;\n    response.verification = {\n      commitmentCheck: \"sha256(secret) == commitment\",\n      resultFormula: \"sha256(secret || entropy || pda || algorithmVersion)\",\n      entropySource: \"SlotHashes sysvar at target_slot\",\n    };\n  }\n  \n  return response;\n}\n```\n\n### 8. **Hono Environment Type Definition**\n\n**File**: `/services/backend/src/hono-env.ts`\n\n```typescript\nexport type AppEnv = {\n  Variables: {\n    wallet: string;  // Set by JWT middleware via c.set(\"wallet\", ...)\n  };\n};\n```\n\n**Usage in routes**:\n```typescript\nconst app = new Hono<AppEnv>();  // Enables type-safe c.get(\"wallet\")\n```\n\n### 9. **Database Access in Routes**\n\n**Db interface** (from `/services/backend/src/db.ts`):\n\nRoutes receive a **typed Db client** with methods like:\n\n```typescript\nexport interface Db {\n  getRoundByPda(pda: string): Promise<Round | undefined>;\n  getRoundByMatchId(matchId: string): Promise<Round | undefined>;\n  insertRound(params: InsertRoundParams): Promise<void>;\n  updateRoundPhase(pda: string, phase: RoundPhase, metadata?: Record<string, unknown>): Promise<void>;\n  insertOperatorEvent(pda: string, eventType: OperatorEventType, payload: unknown): Promise<void>;\n  getLatestOperatorEvent(pda: string, eventType: OperatorEventType): Promise<OperatorEvent | undefined>;\n  getTransactions(wallet: string, cursor?: string, limit?: number, game?: string): Promise<Transaction[]>;\n  insertTransaction(params: InsertTransactionParams): Promise<void>;\n  getUnsettledStats(): Promise<{ count: number; oldestAgeSeconds: number }>;\n  getRecentSettledRounds(game: string, limit: number): Promise<Round[]>;\n  // ... more methods\n}\n```\n\n**Db dependency injection**:\n```typescript\n// In index.ts\nconst db = createDb(config.databaseUrl);\n\n// Passed to route factories\napp.route(\"/fairness/coinflip\", createCoinflipRoutes({ db, connection, serverKeypair }));\n```\n\n### 10. **Error Response Format**\n\nAll error responses follow a consistent pattern:\n\n```typescript\n// 400 — Bad request\nc.json({ error: \"Invalid request body\" }, 400);\n\n// 401 — Authentication required\nc.json({ error: \"Missing or invalid Authorization header\" }, 401);\n\n// 403 — Forbidden (e.g., wallet mismatch)\nc.json({ error: \"Wallet does not match authenticated session\" }, 403);\n\n// 404 — Not found\nc.json({ error: \"Round not found\" }, 404);\n\n// 409 — Conflict (e.g., duplicate match ID)\nc.json({ error: \"Match ID collision — please retry\" }, 409);\n\n// 429 — Rate limit exceeded\nc.header(\"Retry-After\", \"60\");\nc.json({ error: \"Too many requests\" }, 429);\n\n// 500 — Server error\nc.json({ error: \"Failed to build transaction\" }, 500);\n\n// 503 — Service unavailable\nc.json({ error: \"Price unavailable\" }, 503);\n\n// 204 — No content (successful logout)\nc.body(null, 204);\n```\n\n### 11. **Auth Routes: Challenge-Response Flow**\n\n**File**: `/services/backend/src/routes/auth.ts` (287 lines)\n\n**Complete JWT session lifecycle**:\n\n```typescript\n// POST /auth/challenge\n{\n  \"wallet\": \"11111...\"\n}\n→ Response:\n{\n  \"nonce\": \"32-hex-chars\",\n  \"message\": \"Sign in to RNG Utopia\\nWallet: ...\\nNonce: ...\",\n  \"expiresAt\": \"2026-03-25T12:34:56Z\"\n}\n\n// POST /auth/verify — sign challenge message with wallet private key\n{\n  \"nonce\": \"...\",\n  \"wallet\": \"...\",\n  \"signature\": \"base58-ed25519-signature\"\n}\n→ Response:\n{\n  \"accessToken\": \"jwt-hs256\",\n  \"accessExpiresAt\": \"2026-03-25T12:35:56Z\",\n  \"refreshToken\": \"opaque-48-byte-hex\",\n  \"refreshExpiresAt\": \"2026-04-24T12:34:56Z\"\n}\n\n// POST /auth/refresh — rotate tokens\n{\n  \"refreshToken\": \"opaque-48-byte-hex\"\n}\n→ Response:\n{\n  \"accessToken\": \"new-jwt\",\n  \"accessExpiresAt\": \"...\",\n  \"refreshToken\": \"new-opaque-token\",\n  \"refreshExpiresAt\": \"...\"\n}\n\n// POST /auth/logout — revoke token\n{\n  \"refreshToken\": \"...\"\n}\n→ Response: 204 (No Content)\n```\n\n**Key details**:\n- JWT: HS256, `sub` claim = wallet address\n- Refresh tokens: opaque 48-byte hex, stored as SHA256 hash in DB\n- Token reuse detection: revokes entire token family if replay detected\n- TTL defaults: access = 1 hour, refresh = 7 days\n\n### 12. **Health & Status Routes**\n\n**File**: `/services/backend/src/routes/health.ts` (90 lines)\n\n```typescript\napp.get(\"/health\", async (c) => {\n  const verbose = c.req.query(\"verbose\") === \"1\";\n  \n  // Queries DB for:\n  // - unsettledCount\n  // - oldestUnsettledAge\n  \n  // Queries RPC for:\n  // - server keypair SOL balance\n  \n  return c.json({\n    status: \"ok\",\n    version: \"0.1.0\",\n    serverKey: \"...\",\n    solBalance: 1.5,\n    dbConnected: true,\n    workerRunning: true,\n    unsettledCount: 3,\n    oldestUnsettledAge: 245,\n    eventQueue: { pending: 2, processing: 0, dead: 0, completed: 156 },  // if verbose=1\n  });\n});\n```\n\n### 13. **Summary Table: Common Patterns**\n\n| Pattern | Location | Usage |\n|---------|----------|-------|\n| Hono app instance | Every route factory | `const app = new Hono<AppEnv>()` |\n| JWT context variable | JWT middleware → route handlers | `c.get(\"wallet\")` |\n| Dependency injection | Route factory params | `createCoinflipRoutes({ db, connection, ... })` |\n| Error responses | All routes | `c.json({ error: \"...\" }, status)` |\n| Logging | All routes | `logger.info()`, `logger.warn()`, `logger.error()` |\n| DB queries | All authenticated routes | `db.getRoundByPda()`, `db.insertRound()` |\n| PDA watching | Coinflip/Lord routes | `pdaWatcher?.watch(pda)` |\n| Rate limiting | Auth & fairness routes | Sliding window per-wallet + global |\n\nThis is a comprehensive, production-grade backend with clean separation of concerns, type safety via TypeScript, and security best practices (JWT verification, wallet validation, rate limiting, defense-in-depth checks)."}],"totalDurationMs":80896,"totalTokens":66124,"totalToolUseCount":15,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2900,"cache_read_input_tokens":58117,"output_tokens":5105,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2900},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
